00:41:24,400 --> 00:41:25,050
I just

873
00:41:25,510 --> 00:41:27,610
water it every few days.

874
00:41:28,030 --> 00:41:28,780
Only water,

875
00:41:33,510 --> 00:41:34,610
no fertilizer at all?

876
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:35,340
No.

877
00:41:39,470 --> 00:41:41,700
Weren't these planted at the same time?

878
00:41:42,110 --> 00:41:42,570
Yeah.

879
00:41:44,630 --> 00:41:44,970
Well,

880
00:41:45,590 --> 00:41:47,610
mine clearly falls a bit short then.

881
00:41:47,990 --> 00:41:48,570
So,

882
00:41:49,280 --> 00:41:50,130
sometimes,

883
00:41:50,960 --> 00:41:51,780
the more you interfere,

884
00:41:52,240 --> 00:41:53,220
the worse things might get.

885
00:41:58,840 --> 00:41:59,490
Xudong.

886
00:42:00,510 --> 00:42:01,700
I also have to tell you.

887
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:05,610
Everyone in the office felt that

888
00:42:06,280 --> 00:42:07,610
your speech today

889
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:08,970
was highly strategic

890
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:10,300
and politically insightful.

891
00:42:10,630 --> 00:42:11,570
We've all learned a lot.

892
00:42:12,110 --> 00:42:14,050
Maybe my remarks
at the meeting this afternoon

893
00:42:14,510 --> 00:42:15,650
came off a little sharp.

894
00:42:17,190 --> 00:42:19,050
But regarding the Wan Hai case,

895
00:42:22,110 --> 00:42:23,570
your thoughts about it are
both too naive,

896
00:42:23,590 --> 00:42:24,820
and too complicated.

897
00:42:26,470 --> 00:42:27,700
Could you elaborate?

898
00:42:29,110 --> 00:42:30,220
Trying to figure out

899
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:32,300
such a complicated case
in such a short time,

900
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:33,570
that's 'too naive'.

901
00:42:35,030 --> 00:42:35,940
But trying to overturn

902
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:37,700
a case that's already clearly identified

903
00:42:37,960 --> 00:42:39,220
as organized crime,

904
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:41,530
that's 'too complicated'.

905
00:42:43,510 --> 00:42:44,900
Just let Dongping

906
00:42:46,470 --> 00:42:47,570
handle its own case.

907
00:42:48,150 --> 00:42:49,900
Let their political and legal
departments investigate.

908
00:42:53,670 --> 00:42:54,260
Water them yourself.

909
00:42:56,360 --> 00:42:57,820
Just like my tomatoes,

910
00:42:58,590 --> 00:42:59,170
I barely touched them.

911
00:42:59,190 --> 00:43:00,700
But look how well they grew.

912
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:02,530
You can eat it next week.

913
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:05,570
Will you be around next week?

914
00:43:05,840 --> 00:43:06,780
I suppose.

915
00:43:08,240 --> 00:43:09,380
One more thing.

916
00:43:10,760 --> 00:43:12,300
I have to go back to Dongping
tomorrow morning.

917
00:43:13,360 --> 00:43:15,260
The Guidance Group
still needs to wrap things up.

918
00:43:16,630 --> 00:43:17,130
This is good.

919
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:18,780
Finish what you started.

920
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:28,800
[Bus Rapid Transit]

921
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:30,380
Thank you.

922
00:43:34,480 --> 00:43:38,000
[Gate 9]

923
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:50,010
Is this your daughter?

924
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:18,440
At the river's end,
bitter rain and brutal waves

925
00:44:18,440 --> 00:44:22,080
A human life is strewn with hardship

926
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:25,880
Brother, there's a weight on my heart

927
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:29,760
Until I meet Old Lady Meng,
I can't let it go

928
00:44:29,760 --> 00:44:33,480
Since ancient days,
black and white have stood apart

929
00:44:33,480 --> 00:44:37,120
Don't preach
that letting go makes you a Buddha

930
00:44:37,120 --> 00:44:40,760
Even good folk may die unrewarded

931
00:44:40,760 --> 00:44:45,400
So why should the wicked live in ease?

932
00:44:45,400 --> 00:44:52,760
For one last breath,
for one clear principle

933
00:44:52,760 --> 00:45:00,440
For this single rite,
I'll see it through to the end

934
00:45:00,440 --> 00:45:08,560
I will wear my life thin
just to glimpse the snow-orchid bloom

935
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:15,960
I will shred these shoes
and barefoot tame the wind-blown sands

936
00:45:15,960 --> 00:45:23,560
I will face rosy clouds by day
and lift a torch by night

937
00:45:23,560 --> 00:45:30,640
Beneath the bright firmament,
I want every deed bound by law

938
00:45:30,640 --> 00:45:38,400
I want the ones who set out
to return home, no matter how late

939
00:45:38,400 --> 00:45:46,040
I want the rain that falls from heaven
to rise back into heaven

940
00:45:46,040 --> 00:45:53,240
I want to earn my daily bread
while guarding this wild land

941
00:45:53,240 --> 00:46:00,640
I want every righteous path on earth
to stand beneath clear skies

942
00:46:00,640 --> 00:46:08,400
I want the well-diggers' pockets
lined with salt

943
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:16,280
And I want the heartless cheats
to feel the justice in their eyes
